  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Using double-parabola approximation (DPA) applied to Gross–Pitaevskii theory, the interfacial tension of Bose–Einstein condensate mixtures in semi-infinite system is obtained and shows that it is not vanishing at demix state <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>K</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math> , its value exactly coincides to wall tension of second component. A new kind of wetting phase transition (Antonov transition) is also considered within DPA and phase transition is first-order. Antonov line is thoroughly proved, too.</subfield>
